# Dairo + Cloudflare Workers

This starter was scaffolded by `dairo init cloudflare-workers`. It is a Worker
with an outbound send route and an inbound webhook handler that verifies delivery
signatures using Web Crypto (no Node APIs).

## Files

- `src/index.ts` — the Worker `fetch` handler: `POST /api/dairo/send` and the
  inbound webhook handler at `POST {{inbox_route}}`.
- `wrangler.toml` — Worker config.

## 1. Set your secrets

Workers reads secrets from the runtime, not `.env`. For local `wrangler dev`,
copy the example to `.dev.vars`:

```sh
cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars
```

For deployed Workers, set real secrets:

```sh
wrangler secret put DAIRO_API_KEY
wrangler secret put DAIRO_WEBHOOK_SECRET
```

## 2. Install and run

```sh
{{install_cmd}}
wrangler dev
```

## 3. Register the webhook

```sh
dairo webhook create --url https://<your-worker>{{inbox_route}} --event {{webhook_event}}
```

## Edge-safe verification

The SDK's `verifyWebhook` is async and uses the Web Crypto API, so it runs on
Workers with no Node polyfills. The handler reads `await request.text()` (the
**raw body**) and verifies against those exact bytes before parsing JSON.
